						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying by the road-side.</p>						

						<p>RĀJĒNDRA CHŌḌA (II).</p>						

						<p>1170 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1092, Chaitra śu. 5, Tuesday Vishuva-saṁkrānti corresponding to March 24, 1170 A.D. The Cyclic year being the Virōdhi.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Registers the gift of land situated in Moṭṭavāḍi by Pōlināyaka, the ruler of Kūrapāḍu to the god Tripurāntaka mahādēva at Komaragiri on attainment of <hi rend="italic">svargalōka</hi> of his parents and also for the merit of king Rājēndra Chōḍa. The gift is said to have been entrusted to certain Mōdari Bōya.</p>						

						</summary>
